Desert Center first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Desert Center had a population of 256. The population density was {{convert|8.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Desert Center was 173 (67.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 5 (2.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (0.8%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 49 (19.1%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 27 (10.5%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 71 persons (27.7%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Desert Center CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0618982 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 96 households, out of which 14 (14.6%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 46 (47.9%) were married-couple households, 7 (7.3%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 26 (27.1%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 17 (17.7%) had a male householder with no partner present. 28 households (29.2%) were one person, and 18 (18.8%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.67.<ref name=DP1/> There were 60 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (62.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Desert Center CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0618982 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 46 people (18.0%) under the age of 18, 10 people (3.9%) aged 18 to 24, 50 people (19.5%) aged 25 to 44, 66 people (25.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 84 people (32.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 52.0{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 86.9 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 175 housing units at an average density of {{convert|5.8|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 96 (54.9%) were occupied. Of these, 68 (70.8%) were owner-occupied, and 28 (29.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0618982|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715024409/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0618982|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA – Desert Center CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Desert Center had a population of 204. The [[population density]] was 6.7 people per square mile (2.6/km{{sup|2}}). The racial makeup of Desert Center was 164 (80.4%) [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|White]] (76.5% Non-Hispanic White),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov |title=Race and Hispanic or Latino Origin: 2010 }}</ref> 1 (0.5%) [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|African American]], 3 (1.5%) [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|Native American]], 2 (1.0%) [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|Asian]], 0 (0%) [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|Pacific Islander]], 25 (12%) from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|other races]], and 9 (4%) from two or more races. [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|Hispanic]] or [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|Latino]] of any race were 38 persons (18.6%).

The census reported that 203 people (99% of the population) lived in households, 1 (<1%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 85 households, out of which 20 (24%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 37 (44%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 10 (12%) had a female householder with no husband present, 1 (1%) had a male householder with no wife present. There were 3 (4%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[Domestic partnership|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 33 households (39%) were made up of individuals, and 15 (18%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.39. There were 48 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (57% of all households); the average family size was 3.19.

The population was spread out, with 40 people (20%) under the age of 18, 12 people (6%) aged 18 to 24, 43 people (21%) aged 25 to 44, 64 people (31%) aged 45 to 64, and 45 people (22%) who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 47.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 106.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 102.5 males.

There were 140 housing units at an average density of 4.6 per square mile (1.8/km{{sup|2}}), of which 61 (72%) were owner-occupied, and 24 (28%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 9%; the rental vacancy rate was 33%. 147 people (72% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 56 people (28%) lived in rental housing units.

According to the 2010 United States census, Desert Center had a median household income of $27,031, with 28.8% of the population living below the federal poverty line.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov |title=Median Household Income }}</ref>

